1 = \cos y\frac{dy}{dx} - \sin y\frac{dy}{dx}
1 = \frac{dy}{dx} (\cos y - \sin y)
\frac{dy}{dx} = \frac{1}{\cos y-\sin y}
\frac{dy}{dx}=\frac{1}{\cos y-\sin y}.
